(264, 'Responsive Web Design with HTML5 and CSS3', '<h3><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Course Description</strong></span></h3>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Websites can be viewed on a variety of devices, from mobile phones, to tablets, to desktop computers. Responsive web design detects a device&rsquo;s screen size and adapts accordingly.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">In this training you will learn about important issues for mobile-optimized websites. Learn to optimize pages so they display properly and download faster on mobile devices, how to deal with Retina (2x) displays, how to use SVG graphics, CSS media queries (break points), mobile optimized navigation, the Bootstrap framework, and more.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">This advanced level course is for people who have experience hand coding HTML and CSS. Knowledge equivalent to our&nbsp;Intermediate Web Development&nbsp;course is required.</span></p>\n\n<h3><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Who Should Attend?</strong></span></h3>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Anyone who wants to work on web pages or develop web sites. This course can be taken on either a Windows or Mac computer using multiple browsers.</span></p>\n\n<h3><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Prerequisites</strong></span></h3>\n\n<ul style=\"list-style-type:circle; margin-left:40px\">\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Fundamentals of Web Development&nbsp;and&nbsp;Fundamentals of Web Development&nbsp;courses or equivalent knowledge.</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\">A working knowledge of HTML and CSS is important. No JavaScript or jQuery experience is necessary.</span></li>\n</ul>', 100, 80, 18, 13, 1, 3, 2, 'days', '2020-10-10 16:18:28', '2020-10-18 04:06:17', 93, '35f656ba344b3f85abb17f52585cb86b.png', NULL, NULL, 'Exceed', 'Exceed', 'Responsive-Web-Design-with-HTML5-and-CSS3', '88b97389eb50443fb31712eb499e96d3', 'Available', '5062b312cf29ade43141c3a0dedee3ff.jpg', NULL, 3, NULL, '35f656ba344b3f85abb17f52585cb86b.png'),
(265, 'Build Your Online Store With WordPress', '<h3><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Course Details</strong></span></h3>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Here&#39;s your chance to start making money by selling your goods online with WordPress.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Through demonstrations, presentations and hands-on exercises we&#39;ll use WooCommerce, the leading WordPress eCommerce plugin which creates online stores, to build your own store.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">In this hands-on class you will build your eCommerce site and start selling your products right away.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">You do not need to know any code for this class. The focus will be on using WooCommerce with as few plugins as possible.</span></p>\n\n<h3><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>What You Will Learn</strong></span></h3>\n\n<ul style=\"list-style-type:circle; margin-left:40px\">\n	<li>\n	<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Find your theme that is suitable for WooCommerce</span></p>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n	<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Learn how to add and manage your products, complete orders and understand reports</span></p>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n	<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Set up a payment gateway</span></p>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n	<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Set shipping and tax preferences</span></p>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n	<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Learn which plugins are needed to safely and smartly run your online store</span></p>\n	</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Prerequisites</strong></span></h3>\n\n<ul style=\"list-style-type:circle; margin-left:40px\">\n	<li>\n	<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Knowledge of WordPress is not required but it is helpful.</span></p>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n	<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">There is nothing additional to purchase for this class.</span></p>\n	</li>\n</ul>', 100, 80, 18, 13, 1, 9, 2, 'days', '2020-10-10 16:31:21', '2020-10-18 04:05:27', 95, '2fba6ea83f444dd578bec198f5e9e638.png', NULL, NULL, 'Exceed', 'Exceed', 'Build-Your-Online-Store-With-WordPress', '6f4d32619695ad4dcaedf50fe8fb2cb6', 'Available', '6586f558603eddca22026fe52a8b3dcb.jpg', NULL, 264, NULL, '2fba6ea83f444dd578bec198f5e9e638.png'),
(266, 'CA301 HDR Colorist Masterclass', '<p><strong>Course Details </strong></p>\n\n<p>Learn about HDR displays and how to master HDR content. Understand the different HDR formats, including Dolby Vision, HDR10 and HLG. Practice setting up and grading in Resolve on an HDR display.</p>\n\n<p>Learn to take full advantage of&nbsp;new workflows and develop new skills for HDR. Ideal for colourists and other industry professionals that will encounter&nbsp;High Dynamic Range (HDR including Dolby Vision), UHD&nbsp;Premium, Rec 2020, and wide color gamut&nbsp;projects. Experience how lighting, editing and grading are affected and which tools are most useful to achieve bigger better color. Learn the three essential workflows for HDR mastering.</p>\n\n<p>This masterclass is for experienced colourists. but is also of interest to cinematographers, DITs, VFX and editors involved in HDR productions.</p>', 100, 80, 18, 18, 1, 10, 2, 'days', '2020-10-10 17:20:03', '2020-10-11 22:08:56', 92, 'ce2ca99db4871afd46f88a7f10ac953b.png', NULL, NULL, 'Exceed', 'Exceed', 'CA301-HDR-Colorist-Masterclass', 'fecb5f665a738dab02b7b3af40ce68d8', 'Available', '4bd67c7f6ac57e42c9afcd5ab9612fe8.jpg', NULL, 265, '2020-10-11 22:08:56', 'ce2ca99db4871afd46f88a7f10ac953b.png'),
(267, 'RG105 Resolve Color Matrix', '<p><strong>Course Details</strong></p>\n\n<p>Explore all the Resolve grading tools. Learn all the tricks to balance pictures better and faster. Understand the effects of long grading sessions, how to trust your eyes, and how to manage color constancy.<br />\n<br />\nYou will also improve your matching techniques and learn how to simplify and condense a grade or look. The goal is not just efficiency; you will learn how to achieve the highest quality results and eliminate muddy grades. Everyone is encouraged to bring their own ungraded media to use in addition to the course media.</p>', 100, 80, 18, 18, 1, 4, 2, 'days', '2020-10-10 17:29:06', '2020-10-11 22:11:08', 92, '9c6984ae832426b7a80bd9759a89c0de.png', NULL, NULL, 'Exceed', 'Exceed', 'RG105-Resolve-Color-Matrix', 'a0661d13e335d6af1ccf7559db83c7ba', 'Available', '99cf69ae0c961f0155f92c345eea10e8.jpg', NULL, 266, '2020-10-11 22:11:08', '9c6984ae832426b7a80bd9759a89c0de.png'),
(268, 'CA101 An introduction to ACES', '<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Course Details </strong></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Learn the theory and practice of ACES developed by the Science and Technology Council (STC) of the Academy of Motion Picture Arts &amp; Sciences (AMPAS). See how ACES is set to improve and simplify post-production workflow, restore and preserve current motion picture assets, and create a standard that is ready for future technologies.<br />\n&nbsp;<br />\nThis class is suitable for experienced cinematographers, DITs, post production professionals and supervisors. It assumes a basic knowledge of post production techniques but no previous color science knowledge is needed. Netflix and many VFX departments prefer ACES, find out why.<br />\n&nbsp;<br />\nIncludes how ACES is best applied to the DI pipeline from on set to TV set and how it aids CGI/VFX integration.<br />\n<br />\nLearn to use input transforms (IDT), output transforms (ODT) and how to create your own ACES LUTs<br />\n&nbsp;<br />\nA basic understanding of post production techniques is expected but no previous color science knowledge is required. Resolve will be used for demonstration but information applies to any ACES compliant software.</span></p>', 100, 80, 18, 18, 1, 1, 1, 'days', '2020-10-10 17:43:44', '2020-10-11 22:10:19', 92, 'b8cb95d32ea2b848c0eb08c492a5e79f.png', NULL, NULL, 'Exceed', 'Exceed', 'CA101-An-introduction-to-ACES', 'ebc131b0adfb278b52521c6b29e7d8ec', 'Available', '64d9558fbb25340d36efcab46022247d.jpg', NULL, 267, '2020-10-11 22:10:19', 'b8cb95d32ea2b848c0eb08c492a5e79f.png'),
(269, 'CT201 Advanced Looks &Matching', '<p><strong>Course Details</strong></p>\n\n<p>This is a hands-on operational masterclass&nbsp;for working colorists and freelancers. The goal is to achieve new looks from old techniques.We look at grading styles and looks that are frequently requested and discuss how to achieve them, along with the cultural meanings or concepts they impart to a project.<br />\n<br />\nThis course is an ideal follow up to Colorist Strategies or other intermediate classes but is open to any colorist with hands on experience. The class is valid for all grading systems.</p>', 100, 80, 18, 18, 1, 4, 2, 'days', '2020-10-10 17:51:39', '2020-10-11 22:08:31', 92, '6a4ea44ca12876a0817d9796fe275f84.png', NULL, NULL, 'Exceed', 'Exceed', 'CT201-Advanced-Looks-&Matching', '517198b2ab75c531d0e396036ebf113f', 'Available', 'c85e2e5b40453145b0895af67559395c.jpg', NULL, 268, '2020-10-11 22:08:31', '6a4ea44ca12876a0817d9796fe275f84.png'),
(270, 'CT301 Color Design Masterclass', '<p><strong>Course Details&nbsp;</strong></p>\n\n<p>This is a practical masterclass aimed at anyone&nbsp;involved in designing the look and style of a project. We look at color harmonies and balance and then apply the ideas to color grading.&nbsp;<br />\n<br />\nWe focus on the principal elements of an image that clients of commercials, television and feature films all relate to; techniques cover skin, sky, products, mood and time of day as well as topics raised by the attendees. The goal is to manage these elements effectively and efficiently whilst maintaining the integrity of the project concepts and a color schema.<br />\n<br />\nThis course is an ideal follow up to&nbsp;CT102: Colorist Strategies and CT 201: Advanced Looks and Matching, but the class open to anyone with competent grading skills.</p>', 100, 80, 18, 18, 1, 3, 2, 'days', '2020-10-10 18:02:20', '2020-10-11 22:09:29', 92, '55aa17b65e470cfc220cfd5995610bde.png', NULL, NULL, 'Exceed', 'Exceed', 'CT301-Color-Design-Masterclass', '76d146dbd2b1933eb319a9f9ab9e2714', 'Available', '9bd4410895d80d1ebf638f59e94a935f.jpg', NULL, 269, '2020-10-11 22:09:29', '55aa17b65e470cfc220cfd5995610bde.png'),
(271, 'Final Cut Pro X 10.4 Professional (Self Paced)', '<p><strong>Course Details</strong></p>\n\n<p>This Getting Started with Final Cut Pro X course is designed to provide students with the basics of working with Final Cut Pro. It includes a robust set of color correction tools, 360 video capabilities, and solid media management. We&rsquo;ll cover import and export, and explore some of the key features of the software. This is not a replacement for the Apple certified curriculum, but a self-paced companion course.</p>\n\n<p>This course contains interactive lessons that focus on skill growth. The course also contains exercises mirroring the instructor-led version and are performed in a simulated environment that does not require connection or access to a live system which provides extreme flexibility in taking the course.</p>\n\n<p>Web Based Training courses are sold on a per-user basis. WBT courses provide a training advantage for you and your teams, helping you get up to speed quickly. Take the courses you need, at your convenience and at your own pace.</p>\n\n<p>You can start the course at any time within 12 months of enrolling for the course. After you register/start the course, you have 12 months to complete your course. Within this 12 months, the self-paced format gives you the opportunity to complete the course at your convenience, at any location, and at your own pace. The course is available 24 hours a day.</p>', 100, 80, 14, 14, 1, 10, 3, 'days', '2020-10-11 12:30:30', '2020-10-12 09:31:49', 77, 'e998b987d5fcd8c1300f95e06a27f8ab.png', NULL, NULL, 'Apple', 'Apple', 'Final-Cut-Pro-X-10.4-Professional-(Self-Paced)', '50dcdabdfb49237e61fb1f60ded0d2a9', 'Available', 'd66f62b111791b458db3cec2f6ddc6af.jpg', NULL, 270, NULL, 'e998b987d5fcd8c1300f95e06a27f8ab.png');
