(272, 'RG202 Resolve Advanced Curve Tools', '<p><strong>Course Details</strong></p>\n\n<p>This is a hands-on level 2 practical masterclass for Resolve users, but colorists from other systems are also welcome. Everyone is encouraged to bring their own ungraded media to use in addition to the course media.</p>\n\n<p>Custom Curves are not the most intuitive tools, but they are the most flexible and in many ways the most powerful. Indeed, looks like Cross Processing can only be created with the Custom Curve tool. This is an opportunity to practice and master new techniques without the pressure of a client in attendance.</p>', 100, 80, 18, 18, 1, 1, 1, 'days', '2020-10-11 13:11:32', '2020-10-11 22:11:02', 110, '733310077a5418b8ec9619ad8e165f4a.png', NULL, NULL, 'Exceed', 'Exceed', 'RG202-Resolve-Advanced-Curve-Tools', '6295f66bebc6a2f0a19b2cc7c51e2e66', 'Available', '9b93e3271c126e8a0d27112ac96827a9.jpg', NULL, 271, '2020-10-11 22:11:02', '733310077a5418b8ec9619ad8e165f4a.png'),
(273, 'macOS 100: Introduction to macOS 10.15 Catalina', '<h3><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Course Description</strong></span></h3>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">macOS 100: Introduction to macOS 10.15 Catalina is a hands-on class designed to help beginning Mac users and transitioning Windows users become more familiar in using the macOS.</span></p>\n\n<h3><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>What You Will Learn</strong></span></h3>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Upon completion of the macOS 100: Introduction to macOS 10.15 Catalina course, students will be able to:</span></p>\n\n<ul style=\"list-style-type:circle; margin-left:40px\">\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Know the foundations of macOS 10.15 Catalina</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Efficient window and application management</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\">System customization</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Configure user accounts</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Manage files</span></li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Who Should Attend?</strong></span></h3>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">This class is designed for those new to the macOS 10.15 Catalina platform who need to obtain the skills to support other macOS users. This could include entry level IT personnel in businesses that use macOS systems for general productivity or creative design, service technicians who support macOS customers, and technical coordinators or power users who manage networks of macOS systems for their organization &ndash; such as teachers and technology specialists who manage a classroom network or computer labs.</span></p>\n\n<h3><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Prerequisites</strong></span></h3>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Practical working knowledge of computers</span></p>', 100, 80, 14, 16, 1, 7, 1, 'days', '2020-10-11 13:30:53', '2020-10-20 08:47:24', 80, 'b8a4da059dbfac6f65cca1e3fe479397.png', NULL, NULL, 'Apple', 'Apple', 'macOS-100:-Introduction-to-macOS-10.15-Catalina', '905e426ce5a1d3d5e955ccc2ad054d45', 'Available', 'fe65c88ac2d8137675bf37f90f34fdc0.jpg', NULL, 272, NULL, 'b8a4da059dbfac6f65cca1e3fe479397.png'),
(274, 'Mac Integration Basics 10.15', '<h3><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Course Details</strong></span></h3>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Organizations are increasingly integrating Mac computers into Windows or other standards-based network environments. But users and the IT professionals who support them can relax, because Mac integration is easy.</span></p>\n\n<h3><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Course Objectives</strong></span></h3>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Upon completion of the Mac Integration Basics 10.15 course, students will be able to:</span></p>\n\n<ul style=\"list-style-type:circle; margin-left:40px\">\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Integrate a Mac into a Windows network environment.</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Configure a Mac to work with Active Directory.</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Take advantage of network services, file sharing, printing, instant messaging, email, calendars, and contacts.</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Provide security at the user, local-networking, and remote-networking levels.</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Migrate data from a Windows computer to a Mac.</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Back up data.</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Run Windows programs on a Mac.</span></li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Who Should Attend?</strong></span></h3>\n\n<ul style=\"list-style-type:circle; margin-left:40px\">\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Users who bring a Mac into organizations that predominantly use the Microsoft Windows operating system and Windows Server Essentials</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Users who replace a Windows computer with a Mac</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\">IT professionals who support Mac users in organizations that predominantly use Windows and Windows Server Essentials</span></li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Prerequisites</strong></span></h3>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">To have the best learning experience with this course, you should understand how to use a Mac, a Windows computer, and computer peripherals.</span></p>\n\n<h3><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Course Outline:</strong></span></h3>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Note</strong>: The curricula below comprise activities typically covered in a class at this skill level. The instructor may, at his/her discretion, adjust the lesson plan to meet the needs of the class.</span></p>', 100, 80, 14, 16, 1, 12, 1, 'days', '2020-10-11 13:39:27', '2020-10-20 08:00:20', 80, '7dc77552585d11d0e94a61e9675dee8f.png', NULL, NULL, 'Apple', 'Apple', 'Mac-Integration-Basics-10.15', '33b67f8545f4818cdd67237d78b90607', 'Available', '4518eac41967ae6916a5fc879923c565.png', NULL, 273, NULL, '7dc77552585d11d0e94a61e9675dee8f.png'),
(275, 'product name', '<p>asdasd</p>', 2, 1, 31, 28, 1, 3, 1, 'days', '2020-10-11 17:26:52', '2020-10-11 17:37:44', 115, 'a032f993e9a3392e6db045c62d6c7206.png', NULL, NULL, 'zxczxc', 'cxxc', 'product-name', 'f7e4b4aacd596011820a6a81288a463a', 'zxcxzc', 'a032f993e9a3392e6db045c62d6c7206.png', NULL, 1, '2020-10-11 17:37:44', 'a032f993e9a3392e6db045c62d6c7206.png'),
(276, 'CT101: Color Science and Calibration', '<p><strong>Course Details </strong></p>\n\n<p>An introduction to the basic colour science needed for monitor calibration and colour managed workflows. Focus is on practical use rather than math! Find out about delivery formats, display technologies and the difference between TVs and reference displays. Experience monitor calibration in a practical session.</p>\n\n<p>Colorists refer to their main grading display as &ldquo;The God Monitor&rdquo; and there is no doubt that color enhancement is only useful if the display is calibrated in a meaningful way.</p>\n\n<p>Understand rec709, BT1886, BT2020, BT2084, BT2100, and more, and learn to set up and check a display.</p>\n\n<p>Discover what equipment you need to perform calibration on monitors and projectors and how to choose from the diverse products on the market.</p>\n\n<p>Color science 101 is ideal for anyone who uses a display for critical viewing decisions, including DITs, colorists, editors and VFX artists. No prior knowledge is assumed, and by the end of the two days everyone should understand VT 709, BT1886, BT2020, BT2084, BT2100, and more, as well as being able to set up and check a display device.</p>\n\n<p>Topics include basic color science, color gamuts, calibration software and probes, practical calibration, profiles and LUTs. Calman software is used in this class.</p>\n\n<p>If you are considering investing in calibration equipment this course is for you.</p>', 100, 80, 18, 18, 1, 5, 2, 'days', '2020-10-11 19:09:14', '2020-10-20 00:18:59', 92, 'e26db3ab8317550d81ad18c8af58b93a.png', NULL, NULL, 'Exceed', 'Exceed', 'CT101:-Color-Science-and-Calibration', '0697389aaa19a372bc10111a83064349', 'Available', '1091dd2448902e94297517c8fab01a2d.jpg', NULL, 1, NULL, 'e26db3ab8317550d81ad18c8af58b93a.png'),
(277, 'CT102: Colorist Strategies', '<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Course Details</strong></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">This course is designed for industry professionals, assistant colorists, and newer colorists. It covers colorist theory and a detailed look at color tools. It also suggests grading strategies and session management techniques. The course content is not system specific and is useful for using and comparing all grading systems. Laptop systems are welcome in the class. Participants are encouraged to bring frames or clips to discuss during the class.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">The first day covers colorist theories and explains the physical, psychological and cultural aspects of seeing. This leads to an understanding of how influential visual clues are in audience reaction and emotion. The course then examines the film, video and graphics and camera raw color tools that are available and how, when and why they might be used. We then cover best practices for color managed workflows and session management. You will learn about scene referred workflows, ACES, UHD, and HDR.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Certificates</strong></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">All students on this course receive an ICA Certificate</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>NOTE:</strong>&nbsp;This class is recognized by the Motion Picture Editors Guild and their members are eligible to get two thirds of cost of the class reimbursed through Contract Services. More information at&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.csatf.org/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>www.csatf.org</strong></a>.&nbsp;<em>You must apply to them and be pre-approved in order to qualify for reimbursement.</em></span></p>', 100, 80, 18, 18, 1, 17, 3, 'days', '2020-10-11 19:16:33', '2020-10-20 08:46:48', 92, '633bd686c2d31c7185c10353ac576961.png', NULL, NULL, 'Exceed', 'Exceed', 'CT102:-Colorist-Strategies', 'cc28ddc9230455b4f27c27d5e7a76ea2', 'Available', 'cbfdb76fb9ae003204f7969839d167ce.jpg', NULL, 2, NULL, '633bd686c2d31c7185c10353ac576961.png'),
(278, 'CT105 Color Strategies for Editors', '<p><strong>Course Details</strong></p>\n\n<p>This is a hands-on operational Masterclass&nbsp;for editors tired of guessing.</p>\n\n<p>The goal is to get you to understand a clear method of color correction,&nbsp;<em>regardless of which tool you use</em>.</p>\n\n<p>Learn theory and the fundamental principles of color utilizing the Lumetri Engine in Adobe Premiere Pro. We&rsquo;re going to learn how to interpret scopes, deal with shot matching, LUTs, and how to quickly work and handle your material. In a quick turnaround, the best place to work&nbsp;<em>is your editor of choice!</em></p>\n\n<p>Day Two is transferring that knowledge directly to DaVinci Resolve. You&rsquo;ll hit the ground running hard, as we recap the basic concepts and explore Resolve&rsquo;s Color page. We&rsquo;ll also talk about some best practices for handling a round trip workflow to/from Premiere Pro.</p>\n\n<p>You&rsquo;re encouraged to bring a system and some of your own media as well. Take advantage of this rare opportunity to see both sides of the fence from a Master Trainer.</p>\n\n<p>And this class is&nbsp;<em>ideal</em>&nbsp;to get your head around Resolve enough to take other classes at the Summit</p>', 100, 80, 18, 18, 1, 7, 2, 'days', '2020-10-11 19:34:21', '2020-10-20 08:46:52', 92, '9153057b7ef34917dc2821d7b833f8b4.png', NULL, NULL, 'Exceed', 'Exceed', 'CT105-Color-Strategies-for-Editors', 'b811b20935010e10c87caaf313d50290', 'Available', 'ab3432dbaaf02b56f0fafd3e044ee068.jpg', NULL, 3, NULL, '9153057b7ef34917dc2821d7b833f8b4.png'),
(279, 'CT180: Intermediate Colorist', '<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Course Details</strong></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">This is a five day class for those that want a good overview of the art and science of color in post production. Ideal for anyone that is involved with look development, color grading or color pipelines. If you are self-taught or learned from online resources this course will help to fill in gaps in your knowledge and connect information into a helpful structure that enhances your future learning experience.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">We begin with the physics and psychology of color. Learn about color spaces, color managed workflows and the human visual system. Understand the effects of long grading sessions, how to trust your eyes, and how to manage color constancy. Then we explore the way color grading tools work, how and when to use each of them.<br />\nLearn tricks for clean and fast color image analysis, balancing and matching. Take those skills further and discover how to achieve new looks from client references and what makes a look iconic. We discuss the cultural meanings or concepts styles impart to an image or project.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">The course includes methods for all genres from music videos to feature films and from internet, to broadcast and cinema. There is a devoted section to changes that HDR displays bring and you will explore the different techniques and deliverables required for HDR projects</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Whilst some material is provided all students are encouraged to bring their own graded and ungraded material to work with in the class. Resolve systems are used for demonstration and practice, but the class is system agnostic and users of other systems are welcome. This class is often attended by cinematographers, DITs, editors and VFX as well as colorists and we welcome the input from their different viewpoints and experience.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">This class includes elements from&nbsp;RG105: Resolve Color Matrix,&nbsp;CT201: Advanced Looks and Matching, and&nbsp;CA301: HDR Colorist Masterclass.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Certificates</strong></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">All students taking this course receive an ICA Certificate.</span></p>', 100, 80, 18, 18, 1, 11, 5, 'days', '2020-10-11 20:48:22', '2020-10-20 08:46:57', 92, '5f512cd5fd64ab42bea7b7ed94ae8675.png', NULL, NULL, 'Exceed', 'Exceed', 'CT180:-Intermediate-Colorist', '19fb3b3af7f9e716e49a635c68ff5efe', 'Available', 'c6522ccaa8b213b85b1f07a8028acee1.jpg', NULL, 4, NULL, '5f512cd5fd64ab42bea7b7ed94ae8675.png'),
(280, 'CT201: Advanced Looks and Matching', '<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Course Details</strong></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">This is a hands-on operational masterclass&nbsp;for working colorists and freelancers. The goal is to achieve new looks from old techniques.We look at grading styles and looks that are frequently requested and discuss how to achieve them, along with the cultural meanings or concepts they impart to a project. This course is an ideal follow up to Colorist Strategies or other intermediate classes but is open to any colorist with hands on experience. The class is valid for all grading systems.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">The workshop begins with a presentation of standard looks from a historical perspective. It then quickly moves into practical examples and experiments. Each participant can approach the course with their own ideas and objectives and everyone is encouraged to bring their own media to use in addition to the course media. This course is an exciting meeting of like-minded colorists and an opportunity to practice and try new ideas without the pressure of a client in attendance. Take advantage of this is a rare opportunity to sit together with other colorists to bounce problems and experiences around.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">This class is usually taken after<strong>&nbsp;</strong>CT102: Colorist Stratigies.</span></p>\n\n<h3><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Certificates</strong></span></h3>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">All students on this course receive an ICA Certificate.</span></p>', 100, 80, 18, 18, 1, 9, 2, 'days', '2020-10-11 20:54:24', '2020-10-20 08:47:01', 92, 'edfa40cdffdfaffbefc7d25f19b7db31.png', NULL, NULL, 'Exceed', 'Exceed', 'CT201:-Advanced-Looks-and-Matching', '036b08863c0b37fe37d36b8824e19365', 'Available', '411b144e24ffae8b29a30aa59284464d.jpg', NULL, 5, NULL, 'edfa40cdffdfaffbefc7d25f19b7db31.png'),
(281, 'CT301: Color Design Masterclass', '<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Course Details</strong></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">This is a practical masterclass aimed at anyone&nbsp;involved in designing the look and style of a project. We look at color harmonies and balance and then apply the ideas to color grading.&nbsp;We focus on the principal elements of an image that clients of commercials, television and feature films all relate to; techniques cover skin, sky, products, mood and time of day as well as topics raised by the attendees. The goal is to manage these elements effectively and efficiently whilst maintaining the integrity of the project concepts and a color schema. This course is an ideal follow up to&nbsp;CT102: Colorist Strategies&nbsp;and&nbsp;CT201: Advanced Looks and Matching,&nbsp;but the class open to anyone with competent grading skills.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">The workshop begins with a presentation of color harmonies and analysis. It then quickly moves into practical examples and experiments. Each participant can approach the course with their own ideas and objectives and everyone is encouraged to bring their own media to use in addition to the course media. There is a full demo system with panels in the class, but participants are welcome to bring in their own laptop systems to work with. This class is for all systems.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Certificates</strong></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">All students on this course receive an ICA Certificate.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>NOTE: This class is&nbsp;recognized by the Motion Picture Editors Guild&nbsp;and their members are eligible to get two thirds of cost of the class reimbursed through Contract Services. More information at&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.csatf.org/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">www.csatf.org</a>.&nbsp;<em>You must apply to them and be pre-approved in order to qualify for reimbursement.</em></strong></span></p>', 100, 80, 18, 18, 1, 9, 2, 'days', '2020-10-11 21:25:32', '2020-10-20 08:47:13', 92, 'c277fdff7ad1364667c495309f8b1ea9.png', NULL, NULL, 'Exceed', 'Exceed', 'CT301:-Color-Design-Masterclass', '9b6762bb99a8f9808ba256129c2203a4', 'Available', '230b9e22464411dcbb19fa5195f4f74a.jpg', NULL, 6, NULL, 'c277fdff7ad1364667c495309f8b1ea9.png'),
(282, 'CA101: An Introduction to ACES', '<p><strong>Course Details</strong></p>\n\n<p>Learn the theory and practice of ACES developed by the Science and Technology Council (STC) of the Academy of Motion Picture Arts &amp; Sciences (AMPAS). See how ACES is set to improve and simplify post-production workflow, restore and preserve current motion picture assets, and create a standard that is ready for future technologies.</p>\n\n<p>This class is suitable for experienced cinematographers, DITs, post production professionals and supervisors. It assumes a basic knowledge of post production techniques but no previous color science knowledge is needed. Netflix and many VFX departments prefer ACES, find out why.</p>\n\n<p>Includes how ACES is best applied to the DI pipeline from on set to TV set and how it aids CGI/VFX integration. Learn to use input transforms (IDT), output transforms (ODT) and how to create your own ACES LUTs</p>\n\n<p>A basic understanding of post production techniques is expected but no previous color science knowledge is required. Resolve will be used for demonstration but information applies to any ACES compliant software.</p>', 100, 80, 18, 18, 1, 4, 1, 'days', '2020-10-11 21:47:50', '2020-10-17 23:42:34', 111, 'b1bb935a314b28a0ccaf59a2cf8c4fae.png', NULL, NULL, 'Exceed', 'Exceed', 'CA101:-An-Introduction-to-ACES', '14b575add1e03e347e16473ea18e8289', 'Available', 'c8eec1d3cc2e235be14a4920d5067335.jpg', NULL, 1, NULL, 'b1bb935a314b28a0ccaf59a2cf8c4fae.png'),
(283, 'CA201: Color Managed Workflows', '<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Course Details</strong></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Academy ACES</strong>&nbsp;introduced an easy way to work at the highest quality and transform from one large color space to any other. We now have tools to transform from a source to a timeline color space and from there to a display device, making HDR and multiple deliverables much more efficient and creating a great archival format. Color Managed Workflows are commonly used by high end facilities and are heavily recommended by Netflix. They are especially important for VFX heavy projects. Find out more and stay ahead.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">In this class you will learn about the advantages of color management and the difference between scene referred and display referred workflows. You will explore ACES and RCM. You will learn when and how to use both for better quality results and easier trims for different deliverables. Even if you only create rec 709 now, you can still benefit from color management and scene referred workflows.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Ideal for colorists and all industry professionals that&nbsp;work with multiple camera projects, or need to communicate the artistic intent throughout production and post production. The course covers ACES, Color Managed Workflows, Scene referred and Output referred workflows, High Dynamic Range and Wide Color Gamut.</span></p>\n\n<h3><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Certificates</strong></span></h3>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">All students taking this course receive an ICA Certificate.</span></p>', 100, 80, 18, 18, 1, 7, 2, 'days', '2020-10-11 21:58:28', '2020-10-17 23:39:57', 111, '6f20088bc8fa7a9cff264d7fb0ea6044.png', NULL, NULL, 'Exceed', 'Exceed', 'CA201:-Color-Managed-Workflows', '532b86152d7e9ccc35b659ff6d44d3a3', 'Available', '64d7d9575c7cc671002d803d9729298d.jpg', NULL, 2, NULL, '6f20088bc8fa7a9cff264d7fb0ea6044.png'),
(284, 'CA301: HDR Colorist Masterclass', '<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Course Details</strong></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">HDR&nbsp;has been available to consumers since 2016 and is now the expected standard for Amazon and Netflix. Act now, be amongst the first to master HDR. Learn about HDR displays and how to master HDR content. Understand the different HDR formats, including Dolby Vision, HDR10 and HLG. Practice setting up and grading in Resolve on an HDR display.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Learn to take full advantage of&nbsp;<strong>new workflows and develop new skills for HDR</strong>. Ideal for colourists and other industry professionals that will encounter<strong>&nbsp;High Dynamic Range (HDR including Dolby Vision), UHD&nbsp;</strong><strong>Premium</strong><strong>, Rec 2020, and wide color gamut&nbsp;</strong>projects. Experience how lighting, editing and grading are affected and which tools are most useful to achieve bigger better color. Learn the three essential workflows for HDR mastering.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">This masterclass is for experienced colourists. but is also of interest to cinematographers, DITs, VFX and editors involved in HDR productions.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Certificates</strong></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">All students on this course receive an ICA Certificate.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>NOTE: This class is&nbsp;recognized by the Motion Picture Editors Guild&nbsp;and their members are eligible to get two thirds of cost of the class reimbursed through Contract Services. More information at&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.csatf.org/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">www.csatf.org</a>. &nbsp;<em>You must apply to them and be pre-approved in order to qualify for reimbursement.</em></strong></span></p>', 100, 80, 18, 18, 1, 4, 2, 'days', '2020-10-11 22:03:52', '2020-10-17 23:37:18', 111, '9f5bdb1067f9119c670a9a64eef0f9e1.png', NULL, NULL, 'Exceed', 'Exceed', 'CA301:-HDR-Colorist-Masterclass', 'e021a8118d68aad874e7280763eb69b0', 'Available', '839a897780abeea64af46371470b42a5.jpg', NULL, 3, NULL, '9f5bdb1067f9119c670a9a64eef0f9e1.png'),
(285, 'RA101: Introduction to Fairlight Audio Post', '<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Course Details</strong></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">This course is designed for audio editor professionals who work with mix, ADR, and sound design on videos and films. The course is an in-depth analysis of the Fairlight Page inside DaVinci Resolve. Anyone who wants to learn audio editing techniques are welcome, including professionals who already work with oth-er audio systems like ProTools.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">In two intensive days we&rsquo;ll talk about every aspect of the post production audio with concrete real world examples. Laptop systems are welcome in the class.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">You will follow the instructor using the same media used in the lessons. This class is BMD-certified and is ideal for anybody with a desire to learn more about Post Production Audio inside DaVinci Resolve. You will follow a set curriculum in book or PDF form.</span></p>', 100, 80, 18, 18, 1, 4, 2, 'days', '2020-10-11 22:15:06', '2020-10-17 23:35:07', 114, '2c0bab0625560e8e188344e24a620d60.png', NULL, NULL, 'Exceed', 'Exceed', 'RA101:-Introduction-to-Fairlight-Audio-Post', '8e3bc114b09288315d145dceeacea3d6', 'Available', '42c837bccba6b4e4b8b67ad2e629cff2.jpg', NULL, 1, NULL, '2c0bab0625560e8e188344e24a620d60.png'),
(286, 'RG101: Learning to Grade with Resolve', '<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"color:#222222\"><strong>Course Details</strong></span></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">This class is an excellent introduction to coloring with DaVinci Resolve. It is ideal for first time users and you do not need any experience to attend. It is important when learning any software to learn the correct way, that will then form a great foundation going forward.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Class size is normally capped at ten students. Each student gets to work at their own workstation. This class may also be offered as a BYO laptop option.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">The class mixes the operational side of Resolve with real world workflows and problems. The aim is to get you to a standard where you can color a real job. It is run at a relaxed pace, questions are encouraged and group participation is a key part of the course.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">This class is ideal for editors, DITs, DPs, and Photographers, basically anybody with a desire to learn more about color correction.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Instructors</strong></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">All ICA instructors have at least five years experience in the industry. They are working colorists, editors and VFX artists.</span></p>\n\n<h3><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Certificates &amp; Materials</strong></span></h3>\n\n<p>All students on this course receive an ICA Certificate, selected media, and PDF tutorials.</p>', 100, 80, 18, 18, 1, 4, 3, 'days', '2020-10-11 22:20:53', '2020-10-17 23:29:42', 113, '2f6f919d5c2154f9d1fdb0f0514547ff.png', NULL, NULL, 'Exceed', 'Exceed', 'RG101:-Learning-to-Grade-with-Resolve', '1aad7f22bc6803714557bc653ce6f171', 'Available', '6e4d76eb015ff67500039aeb0c9729fd.jpg', NULL, 1, NULL, '2f6f919d5c2154f9d1fdb0f0514547ff.png'),
(287, 'RG105: Resolve Color Matrix', '<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Course Details</strong></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">This class is ideal for all Resolve users &ndash; you do not need to be a colorist to attend. We welcome directors, DPs, editors, DITs, VFX colorists, and anybody that needs to balance, match, and creatively grade images. Everyone gets plenty of hands on practice and guidance.</span></p>\n\n<h3><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Certificates</strong></span></h3>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">All students on this course receive an ICA Certificate.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><em><strong>Note: This class is a two day class.</strong></em></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Explore all the Resolve grading tools. Learn all the tricks to balance pictures better and faster. Understand the effects of long grading sessions, how to trust your eyes, and how to manage color constancy. You will also improve your matching techniques and learn how to simplify and condense a grade or look. The goal is not just efficiency; you will learn how to achieve the highest quality results and eliminate muddy grades. Everyone is encouraged to bring their own ungraded media to use in addition to the course media.</span></p>', 100, 80, 18, 18, 1, 5, 2, 'days', '2020-10-11 22:28:39', '2020-10-17 23:28:02', 113, 'd7fbbbb1cc4cab567a8b7d5d2ef3316f.png', NULL, NULL, 'Exceed', 'Exceed', 'RG105:-Resolve-Color-Matrix', 'e42a52719e65b800a799789f020f4f7e', 'Available', 'ea3af0e5c4a0b3d0cc6ea165f0c6eebb.jpg', NULL, 2, NULL, 'd7fbbbb1cc4cab567a8b7d5d2ef3316f.png'),
(288, 'RG106: DaVinci Resolve – The Basics', '<p><span style=\"color:#222222\"><strong>Course Details</strong></span></p>\n\n<p>After taking this course you will be able to find your way through all the &ldquo;pages&rdquo; of DaVinci Resolve.</p>\n\n<p>What started as only a color correction package has now become a complete post-production program.&nbsp;In addition to color correction, DaVinci Resolve now also includes editing, compositing, sound design, and media management functions.&nbsp;Nobody is a specialist in all these fields, yet it is very useful to master all parts in a basic way so you can solve common image, sound, graphics, and file- format problems without help.</p>\n\n<p>In this three day class, we will spend four hours on every part of the program. We don&rsquo;t pretend that by taking this class you will become a master of all different parts of the DaVinci Resolve system, but you will have enough skills to be able to use all functions and to solve most problems that may arise when using DaVinci Resolve.</p>\n\n<p>This course is intended for editors, colorists, DOPs, DITs, photographers, and AV specialists.</p>\n\n<p>Anyone who already knows a part of DaVinci Resolve and wants to learn the rest, or complete beginners, will benefit from taking this class.</p>', 100, 80, 18, 18, 1, 1, 3, 'days', '2020-10-11 22:37:05', '2020-10-11 23:04:43', 113, 'beaa123970bd960d9e8d5b2065bbc6d0.png', NULL, NULL, 'Exceed', 'Exceed', 'RG106:-DaVinci-Resolve-–-The-Basics', '3d0ae9b6b6a33b06df87d462370058a1', 'Available', '8f6e0a3ff2481e3ff85681ff0119aaef.jpg', NULL, 3, '2020-10-11 23:04:43', 'beaa123970bd960d9e8d5b2065bbc6d0.png'),
(289, 'DV201: Dolby Vision Training', '<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Course Details</strong></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">This is a Dolby-endorsed class that explains the Dolby Vision HDR workflow, from production to finishing and teaches the Dolby Vision tool set. It covers the training required for Dolby Vision facility certification plus an extended module on grading for optimum HDR effect.</span></p>\n\n<h3><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Certificates</strong></span></h3>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">All students on this course receive an ICA Certificate.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><em><strong>Note: This class is a three day class.</strong></em></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">This course is designed for those who are working in or for a Dolby Vision certified facility but who have not yet done the Dolby Professional Tool Training.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">The course is divided into five modules:</span></p>\n\n<ol>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Theory and Overview</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\">System Installation and Setup</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Color Grading</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\">QC and Deliverables</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Test Project</span></li>\n</ol>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">The course covers a full overview of Dolby Vision in the home and in the cinema, the terminology and the content creation process.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Module 2 covers the requirements for color grading Dolby Vision including the HDR display, color grading software, the CMU, and the Dolby Professional Tools. The color grading section includes the necessary image and metadata components needed for a mezzanine file and Dolby Vision delivery. There is an extended practical session to experience the differences in HDR grading, but also to learn how to create the necessary metadata levels, how to get the most from tone mapping with the CMU.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Module 4 demonstrates how to run quality control checks on the mastered material and metadata and we finish with a short practical grade with SDR and HDR deliverables.</span></p>', 100, 80, 18, 18, 1, 5, 3, 'days', '2020-10-11 22:53:20', '2020-10-17 23:25:56', 116, 'db68e5abf1e4e2af48b094efba59b4e8.png', NULL, NULL, 'Exceed', 'Exceed', 'DV201:-Dolby-Vision-Training', '3595c9a34a52d33c2751bd8ac6731c5f', 'Available', '3cf635222051376892b78b4f81817954.jpg', NULL, 1, NULL, 'db68e5abf1e4e2af48b094efba59b4e8.png'),
(290, 'RG123: BMD-Certified Resolve Training', '<p><span style=\"color:#222222\"><strong>Course Details</strong></span></p>\n\n<p>This three day class is ideal for first time Resolve users. You do not need to have experience to attend. The class mixes the operational side of Resolve with practical real-world training.</p>\n\n<p>Easy-to-follow lessons will explain editing, sound, color, and VFX functions available in Resolve. The class is run at a relaxed pace, questions are encouraged, and group participation is a key part of the course.&nbsp;You will follow the instructor using the same media used in the lessons. This class is BMD-Certified and is ideal for anybody with a desire to learn more about post production. You will be following a set curriculum in book or PDF form.</p>', 100, 80, 18, 18, 1, 0, 3, 'days', '2020-10-11 23:12:52', '2020-10-17 23:55:04', 113, 'bc175a978c26db139ddb64dd8f8b148e.png', NULL, NULL, 'Exceed', 'Exceed', 'RG123:-BMD-Certified-Resolve-Training', '8657c63553643bc944ec6811f397714c', 'Available', '461292fee74f8d4a90bb0464fc88bef0.jpg', NULL, 289, NULL, 'bc175a978c26db139ddb64dd8f8b148e.png'),
(291, 'RG180: Intermediate Resolve Techniques', '<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"color:#222222\"><strong>Course Details</strong></span></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Do you use the Resolve software, but need help with Node structure, grading different cameras, and workflow? If so, this class might be for you. It is ideal for current Resolve users or students who have taken our RG101 course, have taken an online introduction class, or are self-taught. It will give you the confidence to take your grading to the next level.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">We cover intermediate techniques using the latest Resolve software that focuses on Colorists who are starting to work with clients for the first time.&nbsp;RG180 also looks at 8bit versus 10bit, 422 versus 444, color space, macro blocking, and general problems that occur during a session.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">We cover intermediate techniques using the latest Resolve software that focuses on Colorists who are starting to work with clients for the first time.&nbsp;RG180 also looks at 8bit versus 10bit, 422 versus 444, color space, macro blocking, and general problems that occur during a session.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">The ICA media used comes from a variety of different cameras, and is not always the best quality so more like the material and challenges we face everyday as a colorist.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">These classes are normally capped at ten people with each student getting a workstation with control surfaces to share. It may also be run as a BYO laptop option. Students are encouraged to bring their own material so they can get individual feedback from the instructor.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">This class is designed around a small conformed sequence that you can take away. We will work through the project from start to finish considering the best strategies to get the job finished efficiently. You will be able to keep the media, project and stills &mdash; a great way to continue your learning.</span></p>\n\n<h3><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Instructors</strong></span></h3>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">All ICA instructors have at least five years experience in the industry. They are working colorists, editors and VFX artists.</span></p>\n\n<h3><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Certificates &amp; Materials</strong></span></h3>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">All students taking this course receive an ICA Certificate, selected Media, and PDF tutorials.</span></p>', 100, 80, 18, 18, 1, 6, 2, 'days', '2020-10-11 23:32:31', '2020-10-17 23:08:46', 113, '4db55c580a1924e4bef8f8a4b3bfb19f.png', NULL, NULL, 'Exceed', 'Exceed', 'RG180:-Intermediate-Resolve-Techniques', '25eb867d3d0641ebc8b493a55153b1a1', 'Available', 'c1cdb77d762d03fdf058107537f1898d.jpg', NULL, 290, NULL, '4db55c580a1924e4bef8f8a4b3bfb19f.png'),
(292, 'RG201: Advanced Resolve Techniques', '<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Course Details</strong></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Ideal for current Resolve colorists with at least one year of experience or students who have taken the RG101 or RG180 class. We cover advanced techniques using the latest Resolve software that focuses on colorists who are grading feature films, commercials, and TV dramas.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">These classes are normally capped at ten people with each student getting a workstation with control surfaces to share. It may also be offered as a BYO laptop option.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">We encourage students to bring their own material so the instructor and the students can grade and discuss the different formats and the challenges they bring. We also encourage student participation and welcome group discussions about media, cameras, and workflows. Get ahead of your competition by learning the latest Resolve techniques.</span></p>\n\n<h3><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Instructors</strong></span></h3>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">All ICA instructors have at least five years experience in the industry. They are working colorists, editors, and VFX artists.</span></p>\n\n<h3><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Certificates &amp; Materials</strong></span></h3>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">All students receive an ICA Certificate, selected media, and PDF tutorials.</span></p>', 100, 80, 18, 18, 1, 7, 2, 'days', '2020-10-11 23:41:25', '2020-10-17 23:05:43', 113, '30600b0cce32fa7dbc8506664862bbef.png', NULL, NULL, 'Exceed', 'Exceed', 'RG201:-Advanced-Resolve-Techniques', 'ca400f04a876bf3328a8450c3969f9a3', 'Available', '5a34544cb50515716d8d457f3aae8bef.jpg', NULL, 291, NULL, '30600b0cce32fa7dbc8506664862bbef.png'),
(293, 'RG202: Resolve Advanced Curve Tools', '<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"color:#222222\"><strong>Course Detail</strong></span></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Participants learn to fully understand the curve tools and how to use them in a range of situations from balancing and matching to LUT emulation and Look generation. The various curve tools can save a lot of time, but also make corrections not possible with any other tools.</span></p>\n\n<h3><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Certificates</strong></span></h3>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">All students on this course receive an ICA Certificate.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><em><strong>Note: This class is a one day class.</strong></em></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">This is a hands-on level 2 practical masterclass for Resolve users, but colorists from other systems are also welcome. Everyone is encouraged to bring their own ungraded media to use in addition to the course media.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Custom Curves are not the most intuitive tools, but they are the most flexible and in many ways the most powerful. Indeed, looks like Cross Processing can only be created with the Custom Curve tool. This is an opportunity to practice and master new techniques without the pressure of a client in attendance.</span></p>', 100, 80, 18, 18, 1, 6, 1, 'days', '2020-10-12 00:11:09', '2020-10-17 23:01:39', 113, '68d93dc0f5e01a9d3e3617b0c35c231e.png', NULL, NULL, 'Exceed', 'Exceed', 'RG202:-Resolve-Advanced-Curve-Tools', 'c1549d940021e02418611c6610e72177', 'Available', '0fda8cefb898748132afa42808b6adb1.jpg', NULL, 292, NULL, '68d93dc0f5e01a9d3e3617b0c35c231e.png'),
(294, 'RG203: Resolve Advanced PowerGrade Looks and Macros', '<h3><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Course Details</strong></span></h3>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Participants explore how to make efficient macros, technical tools for analysis, pre-sets and complete looks that are usable over and over again. A collection of .drx grades and test patterns from the class is given out at the end of the course. Anyone that is not making regular use of PowerGrade needs to take this class!</span></p>\n\n<h3><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Certificates</strong></span></h3>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">All students on this course receive an ICA Certificate.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><em><strong>Note: This class is a one day class.</strong></em></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">This is a hands-on level 2 practical masterclass for Resolve users, but colorists from other systems are also welcome. Everyone is encouraged to bring their own ungraded media to use in addition to the course media.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">PowerGrade was introduced as a learning aid, a powerful macro tool, and as a useful client management feature. Colorists taking this class will create PowerGrades that save time and improve creativity.</span></p>', 100, 80, 18, 18, 1, 47, 1, 'days', '2020-10-12 00:15:35', '2020-10-26 08:32:07', 113, '8daaa21a8869f4897de146602ae1be16.png', NULL, NULL, 'Exceed', 'Exceed', 'RG203:-Resolve-Advanced-PowerGrade-Looks-and-Macros', 'd4e623ba029d052d37049a6914bedeb7', 'Available', '65533b1765bd34dc39d0b38a8d2adf41.jpg', NULL, 293, NULL, '8daaa21a8869f4897de146602ae1be16.png'),
(295, 'RG204: Resolve 15 Refresher', '<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Course Details</strong></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Resolve software is constantly changing and to maximize your coloring opportunities<br />\nyou need to keep up to date. This advanced class is aimed at current Resolve users wanting to learn the latest features. It also doubles as a refresher class and highlights different workflows and ways to get things done efficiently in Resolve.</span></p>\n\n<h3><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Certificates</strong></span></h3>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">All students on this course receive an ICA Certificate.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><em><strong>Note: This class is a one day class.</strong></em></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">The class mixes nicely shot RAW footage with badly shot problematic material &mdash; just the type of footage we might get in a session!</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Students are encouraged to bring their troublesome footage to the class.</span></p>', 100, 80, 18, 18, 1, 5, 1, 'days', '2020-10-12 00:20:54', '2020-10-17 22:57:43', 113, '14bc09f089f16d045f692ccc95bdb720.png', NULL, NULL, 'Exceed', 'Exceed', 'RG204:-Resolve-15-Refresher', 'c545e49bff3846c6766909116ad77540', 'Available', '1e781c09d5c5149b732f8f45616a5238.jpg', NULL, 294, NULL, '14bc09f089f16d045f692ccc95bdb720.png');
