(296, 'RG301: Looks and Matching Masterclass', '<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Course Details</strong></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Students will learn how to bring a movie or sequence to life. They will review movie and drama sequences and discuss how the color and mood has enhanced the film. They will also learn how to create the traditional &ldquo;looks&rdquo; from movies, TV commercials, and music videos, as well as how to match those looks, not only shot to shot, but also to an entire scene.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">The instructor will address the different challenges presented by each sequence or camera, along with the different creative ways to color them.&nbsp;Students get the chance to do the same in a timed situation, just as in a real session, but with the instructor playing the client&rsquo;s role. Each grade is then reviewed by the group to simulate a client review session.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">We encourage students to bring their own footage to work on and share with the class.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">We will also look at the best practices for approaching a session, when to push the grade, and when to hold back. Learn about how the instructor deals with clients in the room and how to make sure they come back. Create established looks and explore how to make new ones. Remember: It&rsquo;s a subjective art form, so just play and have fun.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Here is a sample of some of the media used:</span></p>\n\n<ul style=\"list-style-type:circle; margin-left:40px\">\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Beauty-type TV commercial shot on the BMCC. Great for doing very soft/mist type looks. Great for exploring the Resolve OFX Plugins.</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\">A war sequence shot on Sony F3. Fantastic for a &lsquo;Saving Private Ryan&rsquo; Bleach Bypass grade, a hot jungle look, or the classic Day for Night feel.</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\">&ldquo;House of Cards&rdquo; reconstruction of the classic Netflix show, shot on Arri Alexa. This includes dialogue and re-enacts the original scene.</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\">BMW TV commercial shot on Alexa that focuses on how we can make the car the star.</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\">TV station promo. Ideal for skin tones and matching.</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\">&ldquo;Courtroom&rdquo; problem grading challenge in ACES shot with the Arri Alexa, BMD Ursa Mini Pro, GoPro and Sony FS7 cameras.</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\">A &ldquo;Peaky Blinders&rdquo;-type BBC period drama graded with a soft highlight look, then an alternate hard grainy Bleach Bypass grade.</span></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><em>&ldquo;I really enjoyed the course. This is an excellent class for anyone seeking to learn interesting and creative ways to grade the different types of digital material. The course structure makes it very enjoyable, easy to understand and gives you the necessary knowledge to stand out in this competitive industry. Warren inspires and motivates you to be a better colorist.&rdquo;</em></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Carlos Cortez Climaco</strong><br />\n<strong>Senior Colorist</strong><br />\n<strong>Mexico City</strong></span></p>\n\n<h3><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Who Should Attend</strong></span></h3>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Great for any current Resolve colorists with at least one year of experience or previous students who have completed any ICA class.</span></p>\n\n<h3><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Instructor</strong></span></h3>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Warren Eagles&nbsp;is a freelance colorist based in Australia with over 28 years experience. He started coloring with Resolve in 2005 and loves grading both long and short form projects. He co-founded the ICA in 2009 and has conducted over 250 classes.</span></p>\n\n<h3><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Certificates &amp; Materials</strong></span></h3>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">All students receive an ICA Certificate, selected media, and PDF tutorials.</span></p>', 100, 80, 18, 18, 1, 5, 2, 'days', '2020-10-12 00:27:30', '2020-10-17 22:54:32', 113, '8fff53b56a18cd80395caf37b89759fa.png', NULL, NULL, 'Exceed', 'Exceed', 'RG301:-Looks-and-Matching-Masterclass', 'ebbe28a9d97c671fda30e8ebefb8f184', 'Available', '58d0e9303dc4ff59ad4abb65da25128e.jpg', NULL, 295, NULL, '8fff53b56a18cd80395caf37b89759fa.png'),
(297, 'RG304: Resolve Skin Tone and Digital Makeup Masterclass', '<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"color:#222222\"><strong>Course Details</strong></span></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Learn to manipulate skin tones for beauty and drama. Practice grades that make skin younger and older. Compare the ideal skin tone in different cultures. Skin is the focus of so many images it must be right.</span></p>\n\n<h3><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Certificates</strong></span></h3>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">All students on this course receive an ICA Certificate.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><em><strong>Note: This class is a two day class.</strong></em></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">This is a hands-on level 2 practical masterclass for Resolve users, but colorists from other systems are also welcome. Everyone is encouraged to bring their own ungraded media to use in addition to the course media.</span></p>', 100, 80, 18, 18, 1, 5, 2, 'days', '2020-10-12 00:34:55', '2020-10-17 22:50:26', 113, '62f9d555ec021d74caddfb1e492c4c8e.png', NULL, NULL, 'Exceed', 'Exceed', 'RG304:-Resolve-Skin-Tone-and-Digital-Makeup-Masterclass', '5affac67d3ac551f666788400fe34e24', 'Available', '97bf613b2de1c6b8952485a76083a030.jpg', NULL, 296, NULL, '62f9d555ec021d74caddfb1e492c4c8e.png'),
(298, 'BG101: Learning to Grade with Baselight', '<p><strong>Course Details</strong></p>\n\n<p>Learn how to efficiently set up and manage grading projects in the Baselight system and how to achieve excellent results. This hands-on course explains all major functions of the system, teaches how the GUI and the Blackboard control surface work, and describes best practices for using the extensive grading, editing, and VFX capabilities of Baselight.</p>', 100, 80, 18, 18, 1, 4, 3, 'days', '2020-10-12 00:40:54', '2020-10-17 22:47:52', 112, 'b78df47895a3c8df5799527b5931f805.png', NULL, NULL, 'Exceed', 'Exceed', 'BG101:-Learning-to-Grade-with-Baselight', '5a9094a1cb95e0e56c9e0cc78f13164b', 'Available', '1e493cdfa0100a17dedbf16132189aa3.jpg', NULL, 297, NULL, 'b78df47895a3c8df5799527b5931f805.png'),
(299, 'NG101: Learning to Grade with Nucoda', '<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Course Details</strong></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">The course begins with a system overview, looks at setup and preferences, and basic conforming. It then focuses on the color and DVO tools for grading. Colorists will practice with example material provided, but are welcome to bring their own material to work on as well. We also delve into complex grades, combination techniques, and the use of memories and note libraries.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Nucoda Film Master is one of the most versatile and comprehensive grading systems on the market. This is a hands-on operational course for apprentice colorists and freelancers. It concentrates on the color tools and explains how and when to use them to correct, enhance and fix images. It is ideal for anyone that wishes to work on Film Master or who wishes to practice the essential concepts of grading on a high-end system with dedicated control panels.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">This course is a fantastic opportunity to learn one of the widest color toolsets available in one grading system. It is an ideal follow up to Colorist Strategies, and useful to anyone planning to buy or work on the Film Master family of products. It is also a good primer for those who wish to take further courses such as Popular Looks and Advanced Film Master.</span></p>\n\n<h3><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Certificates</strong></span></h3>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">All students on this course receive an ICA Certificate with Image Systems endorsement.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>This class is recognized by the Motion Picture Editors Guild, and their members are eligible to get two thirds of the class cost reimbursed through Contract Services. More information at&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.csatf.org/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">www.csatf.org</a>.&nbsp;<em>You must apply to them and get pre-approved to qualify.</em></strong></span></p>', 100, 80, 18, 18, 1, 5, 2, 'days', '2020-10-12 00:49:12', '2020-10-17 22:46:46', 110, '5822f3a5cd7b5bab2ca1f32b0d3d6dfb.png', NULL, NULL, 'Exceed', 'Exceed', 'NG101:-Learning-to-Grade-with-Nucoda', '13d8e7d02bb78c8df774604e75a864f8', 'Available', '31f083a0d12c905a96e9211bde9eb78c.jpg', NULL, 298, NULL, '5822f3a5cd7b5bab2ca1f32b0d3d6dfb.png'),
(300, 'DW101: DIT Media Workflows', '<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Course Details</strong></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">This class is designed to keep you on top of the latest technology and future industry trends in the DIT world, while still grounding you in the fundamentals of digital cinema workflows and data management. You will gain a deep understanding of the core concepts and technologies involved so that you can design your own custom &ldquo;snowflake&rdquo; workflow for any production. We will be using and getting familiar with a wide range of software and hardware in class in order to achieve this goal.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">The role of the professional DIT has solidified as the &ldquo;glue&rdquo; that binds production and post-production together. It&rsquo;s a unique technical position that has one foot in both aspects of the production process. As more and more of &ldquo;post&rdquo; moves on set, the DIT is challenged to create workflows that allow quicker iteration and experimentation, in addition to having the principal responsibility for media management and asset protection.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">The field of digital cinema is constantly in a rapid state of improvement and change. New cameras, new delivery methods, and new video standards seem to come out every year. This overwhelming variety of technical formats and specifications results in the necessity of &ldquo;snowflake&rdquo; workflows, where every production now needs its own unique digital media workflow to most efficiently move the camera masters through the production process.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">The class structure will be a hands on combination of lecture, exercises, and workflow defense, and will be held over two days. In order to provide enough time for individual attention, this class will be capped at 8 students. Students are encouraged to bring their own footage for workflow testing.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">This class is ideal for prospective DITs and Data Wranglers, production and post-production professionals wanting to expand their technical skill sets and employability, as well as working DITs who want to hone their craft and learn new tips from their peers.</span></p>\n\n<h3><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Certificates</strong></span></h3>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">All students on this course receive an ICA Certificate. In addition to the ICA certificate, each student will receive a custom workflow consultation with the instructor which can be redeemed up to one year after the class ends.</span></p>', 100, 80, 18, 18, 1, 11, 2, 'days', '2020-10-12 01:00:15', '2020-10-17 22:42:48', 110, 'd45c566fa88ac96886d735a751303152.png', NULL, NULL, 'Exceed', 'Exceed', 'DW101:-DIT-Media-Workflows', '7994959a7207be072f743cc542855935', 'Available', 'f18db310ca7160ff9c2846670ca39a2f.jpg', NULL, 299, NULL, 'd45c566fa88ac96886d735a751303152.png'),
(301, 'SR101: Digital Image Restoration Strategies', '<p><strong>Course Details</strong></p>\n\n<p>This course is aimed at those who want to further pursue the art and technique of digital image restoration. Students will learn about scanning, popular digital image restoration applications, working with video-originated material, restoring Technicolor films, color fading and how to deal with it, fixing scratches and dust busting, reducing flicker, dealing with stains, and much more. The class is taught using a daVinci Revival Pro system but these techniques can easily be applied to any restoration application.</p>', 100, 80, 18, 18, 1, 3, 2, 'days', '2020-10-12 01:18:12', '2020-10-13 00:30:48', 118, 'eeb13d8e5f1921cf187cd9326b1c203b.png', NULL, NULL, 'Exceed', 'Exceed', 'SR101:-Digital-Image-Restoration-Strategies', '35baf371a547e93133a7653cfb01613b', 'Available', '1c586dcd95ccdbad8aba394f78619d5c.jpg', NULL, 300, NULL, 'eeb13d8e5f1921cf187cd9326b1c203b.png'),
(302, 'PVA102: Video Calibration Level 1 Core Training', '<p><strong>Course Details</strong></p>\n\n<p>ICA Video Calibration Classes, Certified by the Professional Video Alliance.</p>\n\n<p>Now 2 levels of training over 4 days:</p>\n\n<ul style=\"list-style-type:circle; margin-left:40px\">\n	<li>Level I &ndash; Core Training (2 days)</li>\n	<li>Level II &ndash; Advanced Training (2 Days)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Level I attendees will obtain an ICA and PVA Certificate of Completion, Level II attendees, who complete class requirements, will achieve the status of PVA Certified Video Professional and be able to offer PVA Certified Video Calibrations.</p>\n\n<p><strong>From ICA, the brand your customers recognize and respect, comes a new professional-level certification workshop.</strong></p>\n\n<p>Join ICA and the PVA for a four day Professional Video Systems Calibration workshop and gain the hands-on experience and skills you need to properly calibrate modern high definition video systems &ndash; practical knowledge that can start generating revenue for your business immediately.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Benefits of becoming a PVA Certified Professional Video Systems Calibrator:</strong></p>\n\n<ul style=\"list-style-type:circle; margin-left:40px\">\n	<li>Obtain the Video Calibration Certification</li>\n	<li>Four instruction days, including at least two days of coached hands-on calibrating exercises</li>\n	<li>Exposure and practice using a variety of the world&rsquo;s best display devices and measurement equipment</li>\n	<li>Access to the exclusive PVA Video Calibrators&rsquo; forum, that provides service menu data and calibration advice directly from PVA Video Professionals</li>\n	<li>Have access to use the coveted PVA Certified Professional Video Calibration logo</li>\n	<li>Offer your clients Professional PVA Certified Video Calibration services</li>\n	<li>CEDIA CEU Credit &ndash; 8.00 units for Level 1 &ndash; Core (CEUP502) and 8.00 units for Level 2 &ndash; Advanced (CEUP347)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Professional Certification Requirements:</strong></p>\n\n<ul style=\"list-style-type:circle; margin-left:40px\">\n	<li>Attend the entire Video Calibration workshop</li>\n	<li>Complete and pass Video Calibration online exam within 3 weeks of your course date</li>\n	<li>Submit ten sample video calibrations for approval via the Web within 6 months. 4-6 calibrations are typically performed during the training</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>About the Course</strong></p>\n\n<p>The PVA Certified Professional Video Calibration Workshop is a professional program designed to take those working with video to the next level. Comprised of workbook focused exercises on the first day, followed by two full days of supervised, hands-on practice, this PVA workshop provides you with the necessary tools to start offering calibration services immediately. 4 total days of hands on training.</p>\n\n<p>During the interactive session you will be working with professional calibration equipment from manufacturers such as Minolta, Photo Research, Lumagen, X-Rite, Quantum Data, JETI, Accupel, and Murideo. In addition, you will receive hands-on training on many display technologies including: LCD, LED, and OLED panels, DLP, LCOS and LCD projectors (with and without an anamorphic lens), various high end video processors, and multiple high end Blu-Ray and UHD players &ndash; all loaded with the latest UHD, HD, and SD test discs. The ICA emphasizes color management systems and how to best adjust them to achieve true reference colors including the use of 3D LUTs (look up tables).</p>\n\n<p>As soon as you complete this course you will be registered to access the PVA Video Calibrators&rsquo; forum,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.professionalvideoalliance.com./\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>www.professionalvideoalliance.com.</strong></a>&nbsp;This unique community gives you key industry information, such as the service level calibration codes needed for top quality calibration, as well as a direct Q&amp;A forum to support you when working in the field.</p>\n\n<p>In addition to being able to offer a premium calibration service, you will be able to offer Professional Video Alliance Calibration plaques including a &ldquo;PVA Calibrated&rdquo; certificate, and a thank you letter from the PVA. This marketing tool can be used to generate additional sales, helping to offset the cost of the workshop itself.</p>\n\n<p>You are welcome to bring your own calibration tools to class. However, if you are interested in purchasing equipment, this class will help you identify the right tools to fit your needs.</p>\n\n<p>For a limited time only, the course rate of $2,499 (normally $3200), includes:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>All instruction</li>\n	<li>Practical interactive exercises using state-of-the-art equipment</li>\n	<li>Comprehensive course book</li>\n	<li>Morning snacks and a full lunch each day (depending on location)</li>\n</ul>', 100, 80, 18, 18, 1, 5, 2, 'days', '2020-10-12 01:27:04', '2020-10-18 04:33:02', 119, 'f85c26c92ff50cc1a48263da963c55b1.png', NULL, NULL, 'Exceed', 'Exceed', 'PVA102:-Video-Calibration-Level-1-Core-Training', '6caa02df654e72761dc2bc71525e38bb', 'Available', 'da42146135f74a18549efc3820fb959b.jpg', NULL, 301, NULL, 'f85c26c92ff50cc1a48263da963c55b1.png'),
(303, 'PVA202: Video Calibration Level II Advanced Training', '<p><strong>Course Details</strong></p>\n\n<p>ICA Video Calibration Classes, Certified by the Professional Video Alliance.</p>\n\n<p>Level II &ndash; Advanced Training (2 Days)</p>\n\n<p><strong>From ICA, the brand your customers recognize and respect, comes a new professional-level certification workshop.</strong></p>\n\n<p>Join ICA and the PVA for a four day Professional Video Systems Calibration workshop and gain the hands-on experience and skills you need to properly calibrate modern high definition video systems &ndash; practical knowledge that can start generating revenue for your business immediately.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Benefits of becoming a PVA Certified Professional Video Systems Calibrator:</strong></p>\n\n<ul style=\"list-style-type:circle; margin-left:40px\">\n	<li>Obtain the Video Calibration Certification</li>\n	<li>Four instruction days, including at least two days of coached hands-on calibrating exercises</li>\n	<li>Exposure and practice using a variety of the world&rsquo;s best display devices and measurement equipment</li>\n	<li>Access to the exclusive PVA Video Calibrators&rsquo; forum, that provides service menu data and calibration advice directly from PVA Video Professionals</li>\n	<li>Have access to use the coveted PVA Certified Professional Video Calibration logo</li>\n	<li>Offer your clients Professional PVA Certified Video Calibration services</li>\n	<li>CEDIA CEU Credit &ndash; 8.00 units for Level 1 &ndash; Core (CEUP502) and 8.00 units for Level 2 &ndash; Advanced (CEUP347)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Professional Certification Requirements:</strong></p>\n\n<ul style=\"list-style-type:circle; margin-left:40px\">\n	<li>Attend the entire Video Calibration workshop</li>\n	<li>Complete and pass Video Calibration online exam within 3 weeks of your course date</li>\n	<li>Submit ten sample video calibrations for approval via the Web within 6 months. 4-6 calibrations are typically performed during the training</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>About the Course</strong></p>\n\n<p>The PVA Certified Professional Video Calibration Workshop is a professional program designed to take those working with video to the next level. Comprised of workbook focused exercises on the first day, followed by two full days of supervised, hands-on practice, this PVA workshop provides you with the necessary tools to start offering calibration services immediately. 4 total days of hands on training.</p>\n\n<p>During the interactive session you will be working with professional calibration equipment from manufacturers such as Minolta, Photo Research, Lumagen, X-Rite, Quantum Data, JETI, Accupel, and Murideo. In addition, you will receive hands-on training on many display technologies including: LCD, LED, and OLED panels, DLP, LCOS and LCD projectors (with and without an anamorphic lens), various high end video processors, and multiple high end Blu-Ray and UHD players &ndash; all loaded with the latest UHD, HD, and SD test discs. The ICA emphasizes color management systems and how to best adjust them to achieve true reference colors including the use of 3D LUTs (look up tables).</p>\n\n<p>As soon as you complete this course you will be registered to access the PVA Video Calibrators&rsquo; forum,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.professionalvideoalliance.com./\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>www.professionalvideoalliance.com.</strong></a>&nbsp;This unique community gives you key industry information, such as the service level calibration codes needed for top quality calibration, as well as a direct Q&amp;A forum to support you when working in the field.</p>\n\n<p>In addition to being able to offer a premium calibration service, you will be able to offer Professional Video Alliance Calibration plaques including a &ldquo;PVA Calibrated&rdquo; certificate, and a thank you letter from the PVA. This marketing tool can be used to generate additional sales, helping to offset the cost of the workshop itself.</p>\n\n<p>You are welcome to bring your own calibration tools to class. However, if you are interested in purchasing equipment, this class will help you identify the right tools to fit your needs.</p>\n\n<p>For a limited time only, the course rate of $2,499 (normally $3200), includes:</p>\n\n<ul style=\"list-style-type:circle; margin-left:40px\">\n	<li>All instruction</li>\n	<li>Practical interactive exercises using state-of-the-art equipment</li>\n	<li>Comprehensive course book</li>\n	<li>Morning snacks and a full lunch each day (depending on location)</li>\n</ul>', 100, 80, 18, 18, 1, 6, 2, 'days', '2020-10-12 01:41:03', '2020-10-18 04:32:24', 119, 'd90769a361bc5fbfb9ac55b23950cf87.png', NULL, NULL, 'Exceed', 'Exceed', 'PVA202:-Video-Calibration-Level-II-Advanced-Training', 'b6d7941343d8e31dc770833c1ff0b050', 'Available', 'd77effd809a3554954b7a22cb950dc6c.jpg', NULL, 302, NULL, 'd90769a361bc5fbfb9ac55b23950cf87.png'),
(304, 'RG106: DaVinci Resolve – The Basics', '<p><strong>Course Details</strong></p>\n\n<p>After taking this course you will be able to find your way through all the &ldquo;pages&rdquo; of DaVinci Resolve.</p>\n\n<p>What started as only a color correction package has now become a complete post-production program.&nbsp;In addition to color correction, DaVinci Resolve now also includes editing, compositing, sound design, and media management functions.&nbsp;Nobody is a specialist in all these fields, yet it is very useful to master all parts in a basic way so you can solve common image, sound, graphics, and file- format problems without help.</p>\n\n<p>In this three day class, we will spend four hours on every part of the program. We don&rsquo;t pretend that by taking this class you will become a master of all different parts of the DaVinci Resolve system, but you will have enough skills to be able to use all functions and to solve most problems that may arise when using DaVinci Resolve.</p>\n\n<p>This course is intended for editors, colorists, DOPs, DITs, photographers, and AV specialists.</p>\n\n<p>Anyone who already knows a part of DaVinci Resolve and wants to learn the rest, or complete beginners, will benefit from taking this class.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Follow-Up Courses</strong></p>\n\n<p>This course is excellent preparation for one of the ICA courses:</p>\n\n<ul style=\"list-style-type:circle; margin-left:40px\">\n	<li>RG101: Learning to Grade with Resolve</li>\n	<li>RG201: Advanced Resolve Color Correction</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Prerequisites</strong></p>\n\n<p>This course is intended for professionals who work in AV and media, and who have basic knowledge of post-production software.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Certificates &amp; Materials</strong></p>\n\n<p>All students taking this course receive an ICA Certificate, selected media, and PDF tutorials.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Instructors</strong></p>\n\n<p>All ICA instructors have at least five years experience in the industry. They are working colorists, editors and VFX artists.</p>', 100, 80, 18, 18, 1, 9, 3, 'days', '2020-10-12 02:09:45', '2020-10-28 08:24:33', 113, '830d66efdb94f54441d2c3f94b32907d.png', NULL, NULL, 'Exceed', 'Exceed', 'RG106:-DaVinci-Resolve-–-The-Basics', '60b0a59292557d9aa0d8bb12d9fe0174', 'Available', 'c17a84c907e6c573ddc23ef187e737db.jpg', NULL, 303, NULL, '830d66efdb94f54441d2c3f94b32907d.png'),
(305, 'RG111: DaVinci Resolve Essentials 1 Day Course', '<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Course Details</strong></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">This class is open to anyone interested in the world of post production. It provides a 360 degree overview of DaVinci Resolve and its potential. In one intensive day, learn how to use the most powerful post production software in the world.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">What started as only a color correction package has now become a complete post-production program.&nbsp;In addition to color correction, DaVinci Resolve now also includes editing, compositing, sound design, and media management functions.&nbsp;Nobody is a specialist in all these fields, yet it is very useful to master all parts in a basic way so you can solve common image, sound, graphics, and file- format problems without help.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">At the end of the day, you will be able to complete a project entirely within Resolve. We will discover how to work within the software by finding the simplest and most immediate operational workflows with which to obtain the desired results. This course touches on all the fundamental topics associated with any project, and utilizes the free version of DaVinci Resolve.&nbsp;You are welcome to bring your computer with you so you can try the workflows in class with the instructor.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Whether you are a beginner or a professional who wants to discover Resolve, this class will put the powerful functions of the software at your fingertips.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Certification</strong></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">All students taking this course receive an ICA Certificate.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Instructors</strong></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">All ICA instructors have at least five years experience in the industry. They are working colorists, editors and VFX artists.</span></p>', 100, 80, 18, 18, 1, 4, 1, 'days', '2020-10-12 02:14:59', '2020-10-17 22:23:07', 113, '1d2a60444596b6ff946fda6b185573de.png', NULL, NULL, 'Exceed', 'Exceed', 'RG111:-DaVinci-Resolve-Essentials-1-Day-Course', '8f30947c6aa92aec8cdd8e812e6754c6', 'Available', '7f1b420f207dfabda473167fe68f0b42.jpg', NULL, 304, NULL, '1d2a60444596b6ff946fda6b185573de.png'),
(306, 'RG112: DaVinci Resolve Fairlight Audio 1 Day Course', '<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Course Details</strong></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">With the introduction of the Fairlight Page in DaVinci Resolve, audio management has been brought to unimaginable levels. Whether it&rsquo;s simple audio mixes, voice-overs, ADR, sound design, soundtracks and synchronizations, or mixes of complete soundtracks, the Fairlight Page offers the best audio tools available directly from within the Resolve system.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">This one day intensive course is entirely dedicated to audio post production. Finally we have a platform that allows you to move all attention from video to audio with a simple mouse click, and this course will help you make the most of it quickly.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Any changes made in the edit are reflected in the Fairlight Page and vice versa. DaVinci is a software that &ldquo;communicates&rdquo; with the outside world, thus allowing it to be integrated with ProTools and other external systems. Exceptional functions such as Elastic Wave and Sample Edit allow you to edit audio with absolute precision. A sophisticated and simple signal flow lets you organize all the tracks in the mix. The integrated effects cover every need and without leaving Resolve we can export the project in many different ways.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">This class is ideal for anyone who wants to work with audio in the context of video post production.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Certification</strong></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">All students taking this course receive an ICA Certificate.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Instructors</strong></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">All ICA instructors have at least five years experience in the industry. They are working colorists, editors and VFX artists.</span></p>', 100, 80, 18, 18, 1, 4, 1, 'days', '2020-10-12 02:20:34', '2020-10-17 22:04:24', 113, '5c1d0176d9f1d7e3bee31a3240900fe0.png', NULL, NULL, 'Exceed', 'Exceed', 'RG112:-DaVinci-Resolve-Fairlight-Audio-1-Day-Course', '2afad6d6eef28ccb92d2ac251c010144', 'Available', '112d730c74bd314e0601a5b8cabd26ce.jpg', NULL, 305, NULL, '5c1d0176d9f1d7e3bee31a3240900fe0.png'),
(307, 'RG114: DaVinci Resolve Media & Tricks 1 Day Course', '<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Course Details</strong></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">In this one day class designed for beginners and professionals, you will to learn how to optimize any type of post production workflow involving DaVinci Resolve, combined with a series of tricks useful in the most varied situations.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">We often ask ourselves how to deal with a new project or how we must deal with a problem. In this class, we will look at many different situations and different requirements. We will see how to best organize different types of production and how to solve common problems. We encourage students to bring their computers with them to practice during the class.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Certification</strong></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">All students taking this course receive an ICA Certificate.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Instructors</strong></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">All ICA instructors have at least five years experience in the industry. They are working colorists, editors and VFX artists.</span></p>', 100, 80, 18, 18, 1, 5, 1, 'days', '2020-10-12 02:22:23', '2020-10-17 22:02:06', 113, '4c5555fe149a2f769841f3a960f8a4c0.png', NULL, NULL, 'Exceed', 'Exceed', 'RG114:-DaVinci-Resolve-Media-&-Tricks-1-Day-Course', 'd29151c08ff5fb8b76f8a7c005deb54f', 'Available', '5df2d2aae45b12cf8d0f8a39fa7be350.jpg', NULL, 306, NULL, '4c5555fe149a2f769841f3a960f8a4c0.png'),
(308, 'RG113: Introduction to DaVinci Resolve Fusion Page', '<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Course Details</strong></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">This class is for fans and video post production professionals who need to produce VFX and motion graphic, or who simply want to discover the VFX and compositing potential of the Fusion Page within the DaVinci Resolve system.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Fusion is a BlackMagic Design software that has also been made available directly to DaVinci Resolve in the dedicated Fusion Page. The main feature is the node operation of the software, which is extremely more versatile than the classic layers. In a single day, discover the fantastic capabilities of Fusion compositing to understand how far you can go with it.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">The purpose of this intensive one day course is to introduce the Fusion Page so that all participants will be prepared to dig deeper into the topics that interest them most. You are welcome to bring your own computer to this class to follow along first-hand.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Certification</strong></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">All students taking this course receive an ICA Certificate.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Instructors</strong></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">All ICA instructors have at least five years experience in the industry. They are working colorists, editors and VFX artists.</span></p>', 100, 80, 18, 18, 1, 15, 1, 'days', '2020-10-12 02:28:20', '2020-10-17 22:47:21', 113, 'f4c11d5b08266bbe710607bf3826ebf4.png', NULL, NULL, 'Exceed', 'Exceed', 'RG113:-Introduction-to-DaVinci-Resolve-Fusion-Page', 'a4063fb887e014253839072f653c6ddc', 'Available', '21505a474c87320d7d506afed8c16c4e.png', NULL, 307, NULL, 'f4c11d5b08266bbe710607bf3826ebf4.png'),
(309, 'SG101: Shoot to Screen', '<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Course Details</strong></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">This ICA class starts with a two or three camera shoot (using RED, BMCC, Sony, and/or iPhone). &nbsp;We discuss how to shoot for the grade and pre-plan shots to make life easier in post. However, this doesn&rsquo;t always happen, so we&rsquo;ll be making some common mistakes during the shoot, and then learn how to fix or match them correctly in DaVinci Resolve. Not all cameras look the same, so matching cameras is a common problem faced by all productions.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">This class is an excellent introduction to working with DaVinci Resolve and Frame.io. It is ideal for first time users and you do not need any experience to attend. It is important when learning any software to learn the correct way that will then form a great foundation going forward. You will receive the footage we shoot so can follow along with the post-production side of the class.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">The class mixes the operational side of Resolve with real-world workflows and problems that often happen while shooting.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">This class is ideal for small production companies, &lsquo;one-man-band content creators&rsquo;, editors, DITs, DPs, directors, and producers &mdash; basically anybody with a desire to learn more about color correction and workflows.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">This is a 101-level class that will enable you to take your projects to the next level. It is run at a relaxed pace, we encourage questions, and group participation is a key part of the course.</span></p>\n\n<h3><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Instructors</strong></span></h3>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">All ICA instructors have at least five years of experience in the industry. They are working colorists, editors, and VFX artists.</span></p>\n\n<h3><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Certificates &amp; Materials</strong></span></h3>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">All students taking this course receive an ICA Certificate and selected media.</span></p>', 100, 80, 18, 18, 1, 15, 2, 'days', '2020-10-12 02:30:42', '2020-10-17 21:55:41', 117, '0f7f80a897457c66388012b7bfc09924.png', NULL, NULL, 'Exceed', 'Exceed', 'SG101:-Shoot-to-Screen', 'cacec82adad894aedfaf81c0efcc5739', 'Available', '18b1c6fee352402bccb0180062ca622d.jpg', NULL, 308, NULL, '0f7f80a897457c66388012b7bfc09924.png'),
