(311, 'CT220: Pro Colorist', '<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Course Details</strong></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">We don&rsquo;t have to tell you how to grade, so we will show you solutions for when things don&rsquo;t work like they should.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">The Pro Colorist class brings together experts in specific areas of grading over two days. This might be learning camera tech, basic VFX for colorists or advanced grading techniques.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Pro Colorist will discuss the challenges of being a professional colorist: how to get the right jobs, what can you charge, how to solve problems that might be yours or your client&rsquo;s. Group participation and sharing of experiences and problematic material is encouraged.</span></p>\n\n<h3><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Who Should Join?</strong></span></h3>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Colorists at all levels. Great if you want to get to the top or stay on top. Remember you never stop learning. Even Roger Federer has lessons!</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">The class will be normally be hosted by two ICA colorists plus several guest teachers to give specialized classes. We strongly encourage group participation.</span></p>\n\n<h3><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Instructors</strong></span></h3>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">All ICA instructors have at least five years experience in the industry. They are all working colorists, editors, and VFX artists.</span></p>\n\n<h3><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Certificates</strong></span></h3>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">All students on this course receive an ICA Certificate, selected media, and PDF tutorials.</span></p>', 100, 80, 18, 18, 1, 7, 5, 'days', '2020-10-18 03:01:55', '2020-10-20 08:47:05', 92, '71cfae1296a40d65e3bcc5e04fb32005.png', NULL, NULL, 'Exceed', 'Exceed', 'CT220:-Pro-Colorist', 'ad5218467920a96dfb6ba3cffec7f269', 'Available', 'a1a84c36e69620732f58a7524e8ae6a1.png', NULL, 310, NULL, '71cfae1296a40d65e3bcc5e04fb32005.png'),
(312, 'CT280: Advanced Colorist', '<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Course Details</strong></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">This is a five day class for those that have some experience working with color but need to fill in gaps in their knowledge of color theory, color science and grading techniques. The course is designed to improve skills, efficiency and creativity as includes learning techniques so that you continue to learn at an accelerated rate beyond the classroom.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">The course starts with theories on the physics and psychology of color. How does the brain interpret visual data? How do we define a color gamut and what are the key differences between sRGB, rec 709, DCI P3 and BT 2100? We then look in depth at grading tools, processing order and the quickest cleanest solution for common grading challenges.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Kevin introduces his own grading theories along with useful approaches &nbsp;to looks, aesthetics and color. We discuss the cultural meanings or concepts styles impart to an image or project.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">The course includes methods for all genres from music videos to feature films and from internet, to broadcast and cinema. There is a devoted section to changes that HDR displays bring and you will explore the different techniques and deliverables required for HDR projects.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Whilst some material is provided all students are encouraged to bring their own graded and ungraded material to work with in the class. Resolve systems are used for demonstration and practice, but the class is system agnostic and users of other systems are welcome. This class is often attended by cinematographers, DITs, editors and VFX as well as colorists and we welcome the input from their different viewpoints and experience.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">This class includes elements from&nbsp;RG105: Resolve Color Matrix,&nbsp;CT301: Color Design Masterclass, and&nbsp;CA301: HDR Colorist Masterclass.</span></p>\n\n<h3><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Certificates</strong></span></h3>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">All students taking this course receive an ICA Certificate.</span></p>\n\n<h3><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Instructor</strong></span></h3>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Kevin Shaw&nbsp;teaches this class.</span></p>', 100, 80, 18, 18, 1, 4, 5, 'days', '2020-10-18 03:10:46', '2020-10-20 08:47:10', 92, 'aca8487822d416e57e63031ee8c46201.png', NULL, NULL, 'Exceed', 'Exceed', 'CT280:-Advanced-Colorist', '0548aee13ea750096aa3f46541e8debe', NULL, '5eea413626f9101701cb543ff1845adf.png', NULL, 311, NULL, 'aca8487822d416e57e63031ee8c46201.png'),
(313, 'RG122: BMD-Certified Resolve Training', '<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Course Details</strong></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">This two day class is ideal for Resolve users who have some experience on using Resolve and have basic experience on color correction. The class mixes the operational color side of Resolve with practical real-world training.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Easy-to-follow lessons will fully explain the Color Page. The class is run at a relaxed pace, questions are encouraged, and group participation is a key part of the course. You will follow the instructor using the same media used in the lessons. This class is BMD-Certified and is ideal for anybody with a desire to learn more about the color correction world. You will be following a set curriculum in a book or PDF form.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><em>Note: This class may be offered in English or Italian.</em></span></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<h3><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>You Will Learn</strong></span></h3>\n\n<ul style=\"list-style-type:circle; margin-left:40px\">\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Balance footage properly</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Creating color continuity</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Working on secondary corrections</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Managing nodes and grades</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Learn how to conform timelines from an XML</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Using groups to manage grading</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Working with RAW files</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Delivering projects, including DCP and commercial workflow</span></li>\n</ul>', 100, 80, 18, 18, 1, 0, 2, 'days', '2020-10-18 03:20:28', '2020-10-18 04:30:05', 113, '2579157a41fd21b9bdf10fd726a0eea5.png', NULL, NULL, 'Exceed', 'Exceed', 'RG122:-BMD-Certified-Resolve-Training', '6cee43cb67bc97850c52446e3a578ff4', 'Available', '0d24234ef778f74cfb3e424c709ee13f.png', NULL, 312, NULL, '2579157a41fd21b9bdf10fd726a0eea5.png'),
(314, 'RG125: BMD-Certified Resolve Training', '<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>Course Details</strong></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">This five day class is ideal for first time Resolve users. You do not need to have experience to attend. The class mixes the operational side of Resolve with practical real-world training that you would get from a normal RG101: Learning to Grade with Resolve class. It follows the same structure as the three day Resolve certified class (RG123), but the five day class allows more time for set lessons and challenges that will test the student. The five day class also looks at some general color correction topics, including basic color theory, RAW clips, and Looks.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Easy-to-follow lessons will explain editing, sound, color, and VFX functions available in Resolve. The class is run at a relaxed pace, questions are encouraged, and group participation is a key part of the course. This class is ideal for anybody with a desire to learn more about post production. The BMD certified exam is optional and will be conducted on the last afternoon. Students are encouraged to bring their own material to practice with.</span></p>\n\n<h3><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>You Will Learn</strong></span></h3>\n\n<ul style=\"list-style-type:circle; margin-left:40px\">\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\">The basic functions of Resolve</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\">How to import media to your timeline</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Getting different RAW camera formats into the Resolve</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Resolve Editing explained</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Adding transitions, text and subtitles</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Basic Color theory and how this works in the DaVinci</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Primary and secondary correction including curves</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Grading RAW files from BMD and RED cameras</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Basic VFX compositing using the Fusion tab</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Painting out unwanted parts of your image</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Sound Mixing using Fairlight</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Ceating Looks like Bleach Bypass or Orange and Teal</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Finishing to Vimeo Youtube or a ProRes master</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Grading and editing challenges that will test your knowledge.</span></li>\n</ul>', 100, 80, 18, 18, 1, 0, 5, 'days', '2020-10-18 03:41:31', '2020-10-18 04:29:42', 113, '6f638faf9dde319589f3a009e173171e.png', NULL, NULL, 'Exceed', 'Exceed', 'RG125:-BMD-Certified-Resolve-Training', '1d1c290185e2a784231115c35ebe2741', 'Available', 'b592a4bba6459c3c1b65d3c394490066.png', NULL, 313, NULL, '6f638faf9dde319589f3a009e173171e.png'),
