(343, 298, 'Familiarization & More.', 1, '<table align=\"left\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:636px\">\n			<h3><span style=\"color:#222222\"><strong>DAY 1 &ndash; INTRODUCTION</strong></span></h3>\n\n			<p>10:00-10:30 Discussion around trainee&rsquo;s background, skills and expectations, industry conditions, workflow trends, history of Filmlight, its products and their place in the pipeline, agenda for next 3 days.</p>\n\n			<p>10:30-12:00 Familiarization &mdash; Trainee navigates pre-prepared scene, grades and compares shots, creates basic stacks, navigates and modifies pre-prepared stacks.</p>\n\n			<p>12:00-13:00 Blackboard Recap on how Blackboard was used in previous session, Identify zones, modes, conventions, modifier keys, keypad modes in more depth, Lunch</p>\n\n			<p>14:00-17:00 Project from scratch Trainee creates Job / scene, locates EDL, browses media, moves media with Flux, conforms EDL, checks against offline, trims an edit, inserts a new shot, replaces a shot, performs technical, match and look grading, using the various primary and secondary colour tools, noting their various controls and behaviours, creates basic selectives with shapes and keys</p>\n\n			<p>17:00-18:00 GUI Recap on how GUI was used in previous session, Identify zones, menu layout, components, instrumentation &amp; scopes, guides, hot keys, view customisation in more depth.</p>\n\n			<h3><span style=\"color:#222222\"><strong>DAY 2 &ndash; TOOLSET IN DEPTH</strong></span></h3>\n\n			<p>10:00-10:30 Discussion around previous day&rsquo;s activities / Q&amp;A / recap<br />\n			10:30-11:00 Visualization Views Menu, Cursors, View Layouts, Preferences<br />\n			11:00-12:00 Media Management Colourspaces, Look Management, Formats, Mappings, Rendering<br />\n			12:00-13:00 Editorial Markers, Editing Types and Modes, Trimming, Re-conforming, Lunch<br />\n			14:00-15:00 Managing Setups DBS, Gallery, Scratchpad, Copy/Paste modes, Selections, Grouped Grading,<br />\n			15:00-15:30 Animation Set, remove, modify, copy and paste keyframes<br />\n			15:30-18:00 VFX grading Stack Management, Keyer, Shapes Sequence Mattes, Matte Merge, Dissolves, Blending, References, Blur/Soften, Transform, Point and area tracking, Stabilisation, Compositing. The goal of this session is for the trainee to grasp the logic governing the downward flow of processes through the stack and apply it in a VFX context, working with selectives, importing textural elements to apply as mattes/blends, and relighting shots.</p>\n\n			<h3><span style=\"color:#222222\"><strong>DAY 3 &ndash; PRACTICAL</strong></span></h3>\n\n			<p>10:00-10:30 Discussion around previous day&rsquo;s activities / Q&amp;A / recap<br />\n			10:30-12:30 Practical Session 1: TV Commercial Trainee locates HD sources/manages data, conforms, grades, interacts with editorial, versions, renders, manages HD &amp; SD deliverables on 30 sec. spot<br />\n			12:30-13:00 Discussion around tools and techniques used in session 1, Q&amp;A, Lunch<br />\n			14:00-16:30 Practical Session 2: Longform &lsquo;DI&rsquo; Trainee organises data, conforms, grades, interacts with VFX, renders, reformats, manages film look and deliverables on short film<br />\n			16:30-17:30 Interop with 3rd party solutions; Truelight,Flip, BLG, Plugins</p>\n\n			<h3><span style=\"color:#222222\"><strong>Certificates</strong></span></h3>\n\n			<p>All students on this course receive an ICA Certificate.</p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 1, '2020-10-12 00:43:55', '2020-10-12 00:45:20', NULL),
(344, 299, 'How to Set Preferences and Install Upgrades & More.', 1, '<table align=\"left\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:5px\">&nbsp;</td>\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:636px\">\n			<h3><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"color:#222222\"><strong>You Will Learn</strong></span></span></h3>\n\n			<ul style=\"list-style-type:circle\">\n				<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\">How to set preferences and install upgrades</span></li>\n				<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\">How to create projects, compositions and versions</span></li>\n				<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Ways to get the most from the GUI and control panels</span></li>\n				<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Primary Tools &ndash;What do Levels, Printer Lights, SOP, LGG, Balance, Color Curves, RGB Curves, Brightness Contrast, and the Channel Mixer do?</span></li>\n				<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Secondary Tools &ndash; What do HSL, Hue Curves, Clips and tools with isolations, such as Brightness Regions and RGB Curves do?</span></li>\n				<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\">How do the layers work, and when are they useful?</span></li>\n				<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\">What can the router do?</span></li>\n				<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\">How to get great isolations using the keyers, shapes and mattes?</span></li>\n				<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Ways to use Blur, DVO, plugins and even regular tools for effect</span></li>\n				<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\">How to get the most from Memories and the Compare tool</span></li>\n			</ul>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 1, '2020-10-12 00:51:13', '2020-10-17 22:45:34', NULL),
